# Zurvan Linux — §8 Typography
# (package-manifest.md §8)
#
# fonts-vazirmatn provides the Vazirmatn family. /etc/fonts/local.conf in
# includes.chroot/ sets it as the system default. (Vazirmatn UI FD, the Farsi
# Digits monospace variant named in the spec, ships within the fonts-vazirmatn
# package — the local.conf selects it for monospace.)
fonts-vazirmatn
fontconfig
